My friends and I stopped here to look for a meal together and I highly recommended it after my last visit which was right around the time it first opened. I was embarrassed to have recommended this place after our service was not it’s best. I work in a restaurant, I know food doesn’t come out all at once and I understand it takes time but this was just silly. Two of our dishes, what should have been quick dinners of quesadillas and tacos took nearly 20 min after our two other friends received their meals. Another reason why I give 3 stars instead of more is when I asked for warm water, you know something you mix with half hot water and half cold water to produce a warm water, I got a steaming hot cup of water, in a glass! Not even a mug... that was placed RIGHT IN FRONT OF MY 1 YEAR OLD CHILD! I was like hold up, let me move that away...Besides all that, the food was delicious! I don’t see myself coming in to eat any time soon though. I’ll probably order through GrubSouth or take out if I ever decide I’m craving it.
